        String query="SELECT * FROM users WHERE username LIKE '"+args[0] + "' AND password LIKE '" +  args [1 ]  +"'";   // Here we are using a SQL injection attack. No use of prepared statements or parameterized queries enabled here because it's not recommended to do so as per the best practices and security advice for JDBC in Java which is mentioned below:
                                                                                    /*  Use PreparedStatement when you know your data will be part way through string, eg., username can contain spaces. So use prepared statement with ? placeholders */   // In order not to expose sensitive user information like passwords using SQL injection attack here we have used LIKE operator only and directly passing input parameters into the query which is against security best practices in JDBC Java
